    <item>
      <title>Version control. Git</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/post2/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/post2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Git is a version control system that helps track changes to code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basic commands:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git init — create a repository&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git add — add files&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git commit — save changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git push — send to GitHub&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git pull — download changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In my project, I use Git to publish the site to GitHub Pages.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
